{"abstract": "Lehman Brothers and Neuberger Berman will auction more than 400 works, many bought in the early 1990s, on Sept. 25.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2010/06/04/lehman-plans-auction-of-its-modern-artworks/", "snippet": "Lehman Brothers and Neuberger Berman will auction more than 400 works, many bought in the early 1990s, on Sept. 25.", "lead_paragraph": "5:23 p.m. | Updated When it comes to untangling bankruptcy situations, art is often collateral damage. That\u2019s the case with Lehman Brothers, which declared bankruptcy in 2008, and its money management company Neuberger Berman. That unit\u2019s senior team has since bought it, but Lehman\u2019s creditors still retain a 49 percent interest, The New York Times\u2019s Carol Vogel writes.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [], "headline": {"main": "Lehman Plans Auction of Its Modern Artworks", "kicker": "DealBook", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "subject", "value": "Art", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Auctions", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Bankruptcies", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Finances", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Subprime Mortgage Crisis", "rank": 5, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Baldessari, John", "rank": 6, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Currin, John", "rank": 7, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Gonzalez-Torres, Felix", "rank": 8, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Hirst, Damien", "rank": 9, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Mehretu, Julie", "rank": 10, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Murakami, Takashi", "rank": 11, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Prince, Richard", "rank": 12, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Richter, Gerhard", "rank": 13, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Vogel